<Base
  title="Disclaimer — AdaptiveResume"
  description="What AdaptiveResume does and doesn't promise: an honest, complete resume built from what you confirm — and no guarantees of jobs, interviews, or salaries, because no one can honestly make those."
>
  <article class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Disclaimer</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        We believe an accurate, complete resume makes you a stronger candidate. What we will never
        do is promise you an outcome — because no honest service can.
      </p>
      <p class="effective">Effective date: 07/05/2026</p>

      <div class="prose">
        {/* ATTORNEY: entity name amendment is currently filing with the Georgia Secretary of State.
             Confirm the final registered entity string ("AdaptiveResume LLC") before publication. */}
        <p>
          Operated by <strong>AdaptiveResume LLC</strong>, a Georgia single-member limited
          liability company based in Marietta, Georgia ("AdaptiveResume," "we," "us"). This
          Disclaimer is part of, and incorporated into, our <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>No guaranteed outcomes</h2>
        <p>
          AdaptiveResume is a resume <strong>completeness</strong> tool. It is <strong>not</strong>
          a job-placement, recruiting, staffing, or career-counseling service. We do not promise,
          and cannot promise, that using the Service will result in a job, an interview, a
          callback, a salary, or any other employment outcome. Hiring decisions are made by
          employers based on many factors outside anyone's control. What we offer is a resume that
          fully and honestly reflects what you've actually done — the rest of the process belongs
          to you and the employer.
        </p>

        <h2>You are the author</h2>
        <p>
          The Service works by finding skills, standards, and credentials your experience suggests
          you may have left off — and asking <strong>you</strong> to confirm, edit, or skip every
          one. Nothing appears on your resume without your confirmation.
          <strong>You are solely responsible for the accuracy and truthfulness of everything you
          confirm</strong> and of the final resume you submit to employers. We do not check your
          statements with employers, schools, or credentialing bodies.
        </p>

        <h2>An AI-assisted service</h2>
        <p>
          The Service uses AI-assisted processing to prepare the suggestions you review. Those
          suggestions can be incomplete or imperfect — they are proposals for you to accept, edit,
          or reject, never facts we've established. Always review your final document before
          submitting it anywhere. On the targeted build, the job-posting match read and
          interview-prep questions are grounded only in the content you confirmed; treat them as
          preparation material, not predictions.
        </p>

        <h2>Not professional advice</h2>
        <p>
          Nothing in the Service is legal, financial, immigration, or professional career advice.
          For federal, military-transition, security-clearance, licensing, or other high-stakes
          applications, confirm formatting and content requirements with the relevant authority
          before you submit.
        </p>

        <h2>Reference data and third parties</h2>
        <p>
          Role and occupation information may draw on third-party and public sources (for example,
          O*NET). We do not control and are not responsible for the accuracy of third-party data,
          or for the policies of the third-party services referenced in our
          <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>"As is"</h2>
        <p>
          The Service and all content are provided <strong>"as is" and "as available," without
          warranties of any kind</strong>, to the fullest extent permitted by law. See the
          <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a> for the full warranty disclaimer and limitation of
          liability.
        </p>

        <h2>Questions</h2>
        <p>
          <a href="mailto:support@adaptiveresume.com">support@adaptiveresume.com</a>
        </p>
      </div>

